Mvp4gException - Exception in com.mvp4g.client
Exception thrown when an exception occurs while executing code of the Mvp4g core library.

You shouldn't try to catch these exceptions because if they occur, it means that there is an error in the application (most of the time, it's a wrong configuration of the mvp4g configuration file).

A message is always associated to this type of exception in order to help the developer to fix the error.

Service - Annotation Type in com.mvp4g.client.annotation
You can use this annotation in the following cases: you want to create a service with a specific name thanks to the attribute name. you want to define a specific URL for the Service Entry Point thanks to the attribute path. you want to specify the class that should be generated when creating the service thanks to GWT deferred binding feature (GWT.create) because the generated class is not a asynchronous RPC class (XXXAsync.java) thanks to the attribute generatedClass. There is no need to use this annotation to indicate to the framework that this class is a service.

Start - Annotation Type in com.mvp4g.client.annotation
This annotation indicates what event should be fired when application starts.

It must be used only on interface that has the annotation Events.

You can only annotate methods with no parameter (ie only event with no object associated can be used).

You must not have more than one Start annotation in a class.
